name: SNS Selfe-service quota management
description: Amazon Simple Notification Service (Amazon SNS) now supports self-service quota management through integration with AWS Service Quotas (https://docs.aws.amazon.com/servicequotas/latest/userguide/intro.html). With this integration, you now can use AWS Service Quotas (https://console.aws.amazon.com/servicequotas/home/services/sns/quotas) to view, manage, and proactively request quota increases, all in one user interface. Your quota increase requests can now be processed automatically, speeding up approval times in most cases. In addition of viewing your default quota values, you can now view your usage and the applied quota values for your account in a specific AWS Region, the historical metrics per quota, and set up alarms to notify you when the utilization of a given quota exceeds a configurable threshold.
